Thirteen-year-old, Enoch Mpianzi, drowned at an orientation camp in the North West. JOHANNESBURG - Parents and concerned parties are protesting outside Parktown Boys' High School on Tuesday. It follows the death of Grade 8 pupil Enoch Mpianzi. The 13-year-old drowned at an orientation camp in the North West. READ: Enoch Mpianzi's father: I need justice for my son Classes were suspended at the school on Monday and parents attended a closed door meeting last night. Enoch Mpianzi's mother, Anto, believes that the school failed her son. She believes irresponsibility led to a school camp taking a tragic turn last week. The South African Human Rights Commission has indicated that it would legally help the family of Mpianzi.